                 <div class="txtNew" data-packed="true" id="comp-irz3dsgg" style="top:262px;bottom:;left:448px;right:;width:524px;height:auto;position:absolute">
                  <h2 class="font_2" style="font-size:17px; line-height:1.2em; text-align:justify;">
                   <span style="font-size:17px;">
                    <span style="font-family:georgia,palatino,book antiqua,palatino linotype,serif;">
                     <span style="color:#FFAA00;">
                      <span style="font-style:normal;">
                       Many hunters ask how our
                      </span>
                     </span>
                     <span class="color_28">
                      <span style="font-style:normal;">
                       <span style="font-weight:bold;">
                        Illinois Outfitting Service
                       </span>
                      </span>
                     </span>
                     <span style="color:#FFAA00;">
                      <span style="font-style:normal;">
                       compares to the famous "Golden Triangle" of Illinois, and that answer is simple. When comparing
                      </span>
                     </span>
                     <span class="color_28">
                      <span style="font-style:normal;">
                       <span style="font-weight:bold;">
                        Boone and Crockett
                       </span>
                       kills
                      </span>
                     </span>
                     <span style="color:#FFAA00;">
                      <span style="font-style:normal;">
                       by county one must take into consideration the land area of the county. The famous "Golden Triangle" counties are some of the largest, and most over hunted counties in Illinois, so yes they will be putting out more
                      </span>
                     </span>
                     <span class="color_28">
                      <span style="font-style:normal;">
                       Boone and Crockett
                      </span>
                     </span>
                     <span style="color:#FFAA00;">
                      <span style="font-style:normal;">
                       numbers than smaller Illinois counties. Our county of Hardin is 5X smaller than Pike County, so don't be fooled by the
                      </span>
                     </span>
                     <span class="color_28">
                      <span style="font-style:normal;">
                       <span style="font-weight:bold;">
                        Boone and Crockett
                       </span>
                      </span>
                     </span>
                     <span style="color:#FFAA00;">
                      <span style="font-style:normal;">
                       numbers per county.  It has already been proven that true
                      </span>
                     </span>
                     <span class="color_28">
                      <span style="font-style:normal;">
                       <span style="font-weight:bold;">
                        "Illinois Giants"
                       </span>
                      </span>
                     </span>
                     <span style="color:#FFAA00;">
                      <span style="font-style:normal;">
                       <span style="font-weight:bold;">
                       </span>
                       come from all over the state, not just the "Golden Triangle".   A lot of
                      </span>
                     </span>
                     <span class="color_28">
                      <span style="font-style:normal;">
                       <span style="font-weight:bold;">
                        Illinois outfitters
                       </span>
                      </span>
                     </span>
                     <span style="color:#FFAA00;">
                      <span style="font-style:normal;">
                       offer several thousand acres of hunting land that is spread out over several counties, but what they don't tell you is ninety-percent of that land is flat, tillable, and basically non-huntable land.
                      </span>
                     </span>
                    </span>
                   </span>
                  </h2>
                 </div>

                   <div class="txtNew" data-packed="true" id="comp-irz3dsgq" style="top:8px;bottom:;left:2px;right:;width:453px;height:auto;position:absolute">
                    <h2 class="font_2" style="font-size:14px; line-height:1.2em; text-align:justify;">
                     <span class="color_12">
                      <span style="font-weight:bold;">
                       <span style="font-size:14px;">
                        <span style="font-style:normal;">
                         <span style="font-family:arial,ｍｓ ｐゴシック,ms pgothic,돋움,dotum,helvetica,sans-serif;">
                          "I had been hunting Alberta for the past several years and got tired of the hassle and high prices of hunting Canada.  I called Wade Gibbons with Illinois' Ohio River Outfitters in 2014 and have been booking Combo hunts with him since. My first year I killed a huge 10pt. with my bow.  During this year's combo hunt I killed a great 8 pt. with my bow and another huge 10pt. with my muzzleloader, plus 3 fat doe for meat. These guys really know their stuff and I would recommend them to anyone wanting an honest Illinois deer hunt. The food is great and the hunting is even better. Thanks guys!! See you again next year."  George Wheeler- Dothan, AL.
                         </span>
                        </span>
                       </span>
                      </span>
                     </span>
